         The book by Mario Puzo and Francis Ford Coppola&#039;s classic film serve
         as dual inspirations for Electronic Arts&#039; action/adventure The Godfather.
         In it gamers can join the Corleone family to exploit loyalties and fear
         as they rise through the ranks to become Don in 20th century New York City.
         Carry out orders, earn respect, and make the Big Apple all your own.
         Featuring non-linear gameplay, The Godfather provides players with
         countless choices for solving family problems with brutal violence,
         skillful diplomacy, or a cunning mixture of both. 
         From mob hits and bank heists to drive-bys and extortion,
